        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-26 17:53:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHow come it was an issue that ConfigBuildingBlocksDataObject needed to implement serializable?",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "5fd9cca8256558341079d216bf0292a4f4ffb0bb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6698,
          "name": "Mateusz Go?uchowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mateusz.goluchowski@nokia.com",
          "username": "mgoluchowski"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-29 13:37:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> How come it was an issue that ConfigBuildingBlocksDataObject needed to implement serializable?\n\nWell, it is because object that does not need to implement serializable interface - shouldn't be forced to do so. This is just bad design and can be confusing for others.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "a9d822f6e5cfc9a4ea5385323d2ef1d6018edbf1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 97,
          "name": "Max Benjamin",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "max.benjamin@att.com",
          "username": "mfour"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-30 17:40:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> > Patch Set 4:\n> > \n> > How come it was an issue that ConfigBuildingBlocksDataObject needed to implement serializable?\n> \n> Well, it is because object that does not need to implement serializable interface - shouldn't be forced to do so. This is just bad design and can be confusing for others.\n\nI think the situation was that the base was not serializable when it needed to be. We kept the refactor internally and it eventually broke our integration tests. I think it's okay to force serializable on these pojos. Most things in the BPMN space should be serializable. There are a number of additional commits coming as there have been a bunch of issues found in the WorkflowAction area. We'll revisit dropping this after all the downstream commits fixing other stuff goes in.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      }
    ]
  }
